snippet.textDisplay:
The US government does its best to divert the world's attention to focus on the coronavirus and to create anti-Chinese sentiments world-wide. Have we forgotten a few months back that a deadly virus called H1N1 has killed close to 18,000 people in the US alone. Moreover, the Trump administration prevented the public health emergency in the US from being declared an emergency. neither do they issue a warning to the world to warn foreigners to stop visiting the US and to announce China-bound flight suspensions.
Coronavirus is bad, but compared with the last flu season in the US it was far worse. The US flu has recorded 29 million illnesses. 380k hospitalize & close to 28 thousand dead with youngest in the list was only 6 years old number to 68 cases.
There are now 38,198 confirmed cases of coronavirus worldwide & more than 900 people have died. The majority of illnesses and deaths are in Hubei province & WUHAN believed to be the epicenter of the outbreak.
Influenza remains a dangerous virus every year and its transmitting speed is faster than any virus and it attacks a bigger group of peoples including young kids & children to adults aged 65 & over. all the dead are killed by flu-related complications.
